Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Taiwan trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The benchmark Taiex Index rose 0.1 percent to 7,662.92.  Solar, LED Stocks: Taiwan plans to allow state-owned Taiwan
Power to raise electricity prices, Hwang Jung-chiou, vice
minister of economic affairs, said yesterday.  Everlight
Electronics Co. (2393)  (2393 TT) advanced 3.9 percent to NT$61.30, the
biggest jump since March 8. E-Ton Solar Tech Ltd. (3452 TT)
jumped 6.7 percent to NT$17.45, the highest close since March
27.  Epistar Corp. (2448)  (2448 TT) advanced 4.2 percent to NT$75, the
biggest gain since March 22.  TPK Holding Co. (3673)  (3673 TT) gained 2.4 percent to NT$458
after the Economic Daily News cited unnamed foreign investors as
forecasting earnings will rise this year on growth in sales of
large-sized touch panels. The company will hold an investors
conference on first-quarter earnings on April 25. Chief
Financial Officer Freddie Liu didnâ€™t immediately answer calls to
